        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 1 at 2:48PM EDT by NWS Burlington VT</headline>
        <description>At 248 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Waterbury Village, moving east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Montpelier, Calais, Woodbury, Duxbury, Waterbury Village, Marshfield
Village, Waterbury, Worcester, Middlesex, Elmore, Bolton, Moretown,
Stowe, East Montpelier, Fayston, Marshfield, Cabot, Morristown,
Huntington, and Wolcott.

This includes Interstate 89 between mile markers 56 and 71.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
